  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "I am making a REST API, which takes a \"block number\" parameter then replays the txs in that block.\r\n\r\nIn order to replay those txs, I need to set the correct hard fork (`muirGlacier`, `London`, etc) according to the block number.\r\n\r\nFrom what I learned from the document, the hard fork is set in the configuration file, and is not possible to change during run-time.\r\n\r\nIs there any workaround available to me? Or can I make this feature request?",
